# FYA Core Standards

- Keep the app name and messaging as `FYA (Found Your Animal)`.
- Stack baseline is fixed: Next.js App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind + shadcn.
- Auth must use `@supabase/ssr` utilities from `lib/supabase/*` (no legacy auth-helpers).
- Roles are `admin`, `user`, `canil` and authorization must depend on `profiles.role`.
- Route protection must remain enforced in `middleware.ts`.
- New features must preserve PT/EN compatibility and locale-aware navigation (`/pt`, `/en`).
- Prefer Server Components by default; use Client Components only when necessary.
- Keep changes small, testable, and aligned with existing file structure.
